inn1.comm: goes back and defends
worked off the hips into the leg side to open his account
Anamul is slow in getting forward to a pitched-up delivery on off before prodding it to cover
beaten outside off as the length is a touch shorter and there is considerable movement and bounce away from Anamul's flailing blade
gets forward on off and defends firmly this time
gets forward and slices it down to third man
short outside off and cut firmly in front of point
full and swinging down leg as it strikes the pad outside leg
pushed wide of off and called
beautifully stroked on bent knee through the covers and races away
squeezed out off the pads to leg
shorter length on leg, he goes forward and is beaten and strikes him on the back pad
banged in on off and easily ducks underneath
full and nipping in and takes the inside edge before it strikes the pad
left alone outside off as it rears alarmingly from a good length and McCullum has to leap high with one hand to collect
defends from the crease on off
perfectly placed French cut as Tamim doesn't move the feet and lazily pushes the hands at one zipping back in and bouncing on middle, it races away fine
fuller and again inside edges into pad as an appeal is stifled
this time he beats the bat and hits pad in front of the stumps! Again gets it to swing back and strike on middle and leg, umpire was confident in raising the gfinger
hops back into the crease to defend a good length delivery on middle
short and wide outside off and he jumps to slap an uppercut over backward point and it races away to the fence

firmly drives down to mid-off who dives well to cut it off, in the meantime the batsmen have had a colossal collapse in communication, Anamul set off with the shot, Mominul initially moved forward, then he started to run but Anamul decided to turn around at the same time and they both ended up at the striker's end as the bowler whips the bails off, Anamul reached the crease first so Mominul departs for a diamond duck
played down to third man
banged in well down leg and sails far too high to avoid being wided
worked off the pads fine
banged in on middle and defended by going right back and dropping at his feet
slips well down leg and a loud appeal obscures the fact that no contact with bat or pad was made so the ball is inexpiclably not wided
left alone outside off
worked from a short length off middle to leg
left alone outside off as it moves away a touch
oversteps and concedes a free hit
follows up with a good delivery in the blockhole outside off which he can't lay bat on
starts with a wide well down leg
defends on the front foot
drives firmly to short cover
defends solidly on middle
drives down to mid-off
strays on leg and clipped away to backward square
worked off middle and makes fine leg work to cut it off
defends from the crease solidly
left alone outside off
lovely delivery on off which just seamed away a touch and again the bounce undid the batsman as he pushed forward and it struck high on the splice and carried nicely to second slip
gets forward to defend on off
this zips back off the pitch on middle and is awkwardly jammed out from the crease
goes back in the crease and is struck on the pads as an appeal is belted out, hint of inside edge there
worked to leg
pushed down to mid-off
goes back and punches into the covers
takes the risk of giving some room to launch a full ball over mid-off just out of reach of the diving fielder and the risk pays off
worked to leg
nicely struck off the front foot as Neesham strays outside off and Mushfiqur slaps it away past a diving cover
beats the outside edge as he is drawn forward on off to defend
defends a full ball on middle down the pitch
outside off and left alone
defended with the full face of the blade on middle
beaten outside off as Naeem tries to pull the Neil McKenzie curtain-rail leave on it but does so too late
maiden as it angles into Naeem who can only defend to mid-on
strays again onto the pads and clipped to deep square
worked off the pads to midwicket
throws the hands at one well outside off and isn't close to making contact
again goes for an expansive drive without moving the feet and is beaten
defends down the pitch
angled across the batsman and left alone
firmly punched to the short cover
worked off the pads behind square
mistimes the drive down to mid-off
slips this wide well down leg
cuts a short wide ball straight to point
beaten outside off as it nips away fractionally after Mushfiqur was forward to defend
goes back and defends into the pitch
short down leg, tries to clip it away, flicks the shirt and rolls to McCullum behind the sticks
pushed through wide of off and an extra is added to the total
defends off the back foot to point
again defends with an open face to point
short outside off and cut down to third man
superb dive by Neesham on the third man boundary prevents four after a fierce cut to a short ball outside off
short outside off and this time pummelled in front of square on the off side and it races to the fence
around the wicket and he eases it down to third man
defends into the covers where Nathan McCullum, usually an excellent fielder, makes a hash of a simple stop and allows Naeem to get off the mark after 16 scoreless deliveries
drives a slower ball from out of the knuckles into the covers
played down to midwicket
defends to leg as Corey Anderson comes on
short and wide and cut solidly but picks out point
worked to midwicket off the pads
defends to off and looks to get off strike but can't
again defends solidly
full on middle and played back to the bowler
tucked with the turn to backward square
full outside off and Mushfiqur gets down to slog sweep handsomely over the cow corner boundary and bring up the 50 for Bangladesh
firmly driven to short cover
goes down again for another slog sweep but this was too short and it bobbled past the stroke and into the back pad
fired into leg and tucked off the pads
beauty on middle and leg which just zips across a touch as the batsman gropes, keeper appeals but is on his own there
digs out a full ball on off and sets off immediately with the stroke as mid-off collects
down leg and clipoped fine
banged in short on off and hooked out to deep backward square
played into the off side
full on leg and tucked into the leg side, Naeem sets off but his skipper is uninterested until suddenly deciding there might be a run there by which time Naeem is against the run
worked off the pads fine
almost another mix up as he taps into the covers and sets off before stopping, luckily Mushfiqur is an energizer bunny who can scamper back in time
beaten outside off as he just throws the hands at one turning back in without moving the feet
breaks the shackles by advancing and converting a delivery outside off into a full toss which is firmly put away to the cover boundary
defended awkwardly to leg
eased down to third man
beaten outside off as he tries to cut without any feet movement
touch of bounce outside off as Naeem manages to chop one down to third man
waits in the crease before reaching across and dabbing down to third man
played fine off the pads
swats a good length ball on middle wide of mid-on and out to the cow corner boundary
drives to long-on after using the feet
tapped away square on the leg side
comes down the track and crashes a drive through extra cover to pick up his second boundary
arm ball slides on outside off past the attempted glide
forward to defend to third man and is quickly sent back
beaten by one which drifts away before turning in as Naeem prods the blade at it without making contact
starts short outside off and cut to point's right but the fielder does well to pull off a partial stop
forward to defend on off as it slides on
gets forward to defend to cover
goes back and cuts out to deep point
slides down leg past the flick
slides on outside off and keeps low as he is beaten trying to cut
pushed through on off and defended
forward to defend into the covers and again a running mix-up occurs as Naeem scurries back

Kane Williamson chases hard from third man and dives well on the rope to haul it in after Mushfiqur was surprised by the bounce from around the wicket as it reared on him and he could only stab it involuntarily through slip
winds up and launches into a cover drive which goes out to the sweeper
uses his feet to come down the track to the pitch of the ball and lofts it over mid-off and out to the rope after a few bounces to reach a well-made 50 after coming into a poor situation
almost gives it away as he goes down and top-edges a slog sweep and it lands just short of long-on running in
forward and defends into the covers with soft hands
cut out to the cover sweeper
beaten outside off trying to slog sweep again, almost hits off stump
worked slightly wide of mid-on
short outside off and cut to deep point
well worked into the space at midwicket to beat the bowler who runs across to collect
played into the covers
worked off the pads into the midwicket region
another run-out opportunity as he drives into the covers and sets off, some hesitation as Naeem has to scramble home
another mix-up as Mushfiqur tucks off the pads and sets off before being sent back, but the throw eludes McCullum and the fielder backing up and they steal an overthrow
tapped into the covers
short outside off and chops a cut past backward point nicely
on leg and worked to square leg
in the blockhole and dug out
gets down and slog sweeps well over mid-on and it lands just inside the rope at long-on
tucked off the pads to leg
full toss smashed back past the bowler and down to the straight boundary
short long hop outside off and Naeem rocks back to cut powerfully in front of point and it beats the sweeper
tucked to backward square and Mushfiqur is quickly sent back
full on leg and worked to deep backward square
forced back into the crease and he defends to leg
gets forward to defend to cover
softly defends square and no run is forthcoming
full outside off and launched to the cover sweeper
strays down leg and helped on its way with a firm flick fine
defends to leg
worked into the covers
tries to dab outside off as Williamson angles it across from around the wicket and slides it past the stroke
digs out a full ball to leg
chopped down to third man
down leg and tucked fine
outside off and he reaches for it and toes it through the slips down to the third man fence
chopped over point into the deep
defends to point
borderline outside off which is deemed by the umpire to have strayed into wide territory
beaten outside off as he attempted a slog

shortish slower ball outside off, Razzak moves across to pull, strikes the thigh pad and balloons up behind the wicket as they set off, Brendon McCullum puts in a superlative dive to pull off a great catch, the only issue being there was no contact with bat or glove as the umpire nevertheless sends the batsman packing

inn2.comm: short of a good length delivery on the leg stump. Rutherford turns it to square-leg
width given outside the off stump, but a little more bounce this time as Rutherford stands tall and punches it to cover
good length ball outside the off stump. Rutherford defends it to the off side
good length ball on the off stump. Rutherford comes forward and punches it to cover
fuller ball outside the off stump. Rutherford gets the width he is looking for and drives, but can't pierce the gap in the point region
good length ball and slower in pace. Rutherford adjusts and pushes it back to the bowler, who does well to stop it. There is a huge roar as the dot ball ensures that the first over is a maiden
comes forward and punches it to point
good length ball on the off stump. Devcich defends it to the off side
width outside the off stump. Devcich rocks back and slams it past the cover fielder for a boundary. What a way to get first runs in international cricket
comes forward and pushes it back to the bowler
struck on the pads outside the off stump. There was a huge appeal. The umpire would find it tough to give it, even with a fifth stump
comes forward and drives it to mid-on
fuller ball on the off stump. Rutherford pushes it to wide mid-on and sets off for a quick single
fuller ball outside the off stump. Devcich drives it to mid-off
short ball outside the off stump. Moving away a touch. Bounce there, as Devcich looks to defend and is beaten by the away movement
moving away a touch after pitching.This time, there is width to tempt him drive, which he does, but is beaten
fuller and wider outside the off stump. Devcich drives and connects this time as he smashes it past cover for the second time to get his second boundary

that's the first wicket! Gazi bowls it outside the off stump, enough to have Rutherford swinging after it. He misses and the ball comes in with the angle and hits the leg stump and the collective noise at the ground raises by at least 1000 decibels
fuller ball outside the off stump. Elliot is drawn forward and only manages an outside edge past the first slip for a boundary
comes forward and defends it to the leg side
flighted ball on the middle stump. Elliot skips down the track and turns it to short fine-leg
fuller ball outside the off stump. Elliot pushes it back to the bowler
pacy delivery on the leg stump. Devcich looks to play it on the leg side and closes the face of the bat early. He is deceived by the bounce and gets an outside edge to third-man for a single
comes forward and pushes it to mid-on for a single
fuller ball on the middle and leg. Devcich defends it to the leg side
good length ball outside the off stump. Devcich opens the face of the bat and steers it to third-man for a single
comes forward and pushes it to mid-on
fuller ball outside the off stump. Elliot comes forward and defends it to the off side
comes forward and drives it to mid-off for a single
defends it to the leg side
fuller ball outside the off stump. Doesn't turn. Elliot is playing for the turn and is beaten
reaches out and drives it to mid-off
wide down the leg side
drives it to long-on for a single and retains the strike
good length ball outside the off stump. Elliot drives it to cover
short ball on the off stump. Elliot drives it to long-off for a single
drives it to sweeper cover for a single
comes forward and turns it to square-leg for a single
short of a good length delivery. Devcich pushes it to the leg side
defends it to the off side
short ball outside the off stump. Devcich clears the front foot and attempts to get a third boundary through the covers, but the fielder pulls off a diving stop and saves three runs
comes forward and defends it to the off side
pushes it to cover
good length ball outside the off stump. Elliot plays it with soft hands to short third-man for a single
short ball on the off stump. Elliot pulls it to deep mid wicket for a couple
pushes it to the leg side for a single
fuller ball outside the off stump. Devcich stands tall and drives it past point for a boundary
similar ball and similar shot. This time he doesn't find the gap at point
good length ball on the middle stump. Devcich pushes it back to the bowler
comes forward and turns it to the leg side
comes forward and punches it to mid-on for a single
fuller ball outside the off stump. Devcich drives it to point
short ball outside the off stump. Devcich makes room and cuts it in the gap between point and cover for a boundary
comes forward and drives it to mid-on
fuller ball on the off stump. Devcich comes forward and looks to drive it. He is beaten by the turn
short ball on the off stump. Elliot defends it back to the bowler
struck on the thigh pad and the ball runs away to third-man for a leg-bye
strays down the leg stump line. Devcich looks to work it away and is struck on the pads as they run a leg-bye
good length ball outside the off stump. Elliot comes forward and defends it back to the bowler
short ball on the off stump. Elliot stays on the backfoot and defends it back to the bowler
comes forward and drives it to mid-off for a single
turns it to square-leg for a single
comes forward and drives it to sweeper cover for a single
turns it to short fine-leg for a single

good length ball on the off stump. Devcich, after playing all those delightful strokes on the off side tries to get ugly by looking to slog across the line and is beaten. Pretty similar dismissal to Rutherford. The crowd rise up in unison
comes forward and pushes it to the leg side
comes forward and turns it to the leg side
strays on the leg stump line. He turns it to fine-leg for a single
good length ball outside the off stump. Taylor defends it to the leg side
comes forward and drives it to mid-off. Tamim lets rip a throw and hits the stumps
fuller ball outside the off stump. Taylor looks to slice it and gets an inside edge to fine-leg for a boundary. Mortaza has a look of despair on his face
short ball on the off stump. Taylor stays back and cuts it. He gets a top edge over first slip for a boundary.
comes forward and defends it back to the bowler
comes forward and pushes it back to the bowler
comes down the track and pushes it back onto the pitch
comes forward and pushes it to the leg side
on the leg stump. Elliot sweeps it powerfully past square-leg for a boundary
comes forward and turns it to mid wicket region for a single
fuller ball on the leg stump. Elliot turns it to the leg side where Naeem Islam pulls off a brilliant save
short ball outside the off stump. Elliot looks to defend it and is beaten by the away movement
comes forward and pushes it back to the bowler
short ball outside the off stump. Elliot moves across and cuts it to point. There was a boundary for the taking there but Elliot doesn't find the gap
comes forward and defends it to the off side
comes forward and drives it to cover
fuller ball outside the off stump. Taylor pushes it back to the bowler
off the outside edge to short third-man
comes forward and pushes it to the leg side
fuller ball on the off stump. Taylor pushes it back to the bowler
defends it to the off side
pushes it to the leg side for a single

good length ball pitching on the middle stump and moving away. Taylor is looking to steer it and gets an outside edge. Rahim accepts it with glee as he knows that Taylor can take the game away from them quickly. Rubel, like Mahmudullah and Gazi strikes early
comes forward and drives it back to the bowler
stays on the backfoot and punches it to cover
outside the off stump. Anderson looks to drive and is beaten by the away movement
on the middle stump. Elliot turns it to mid wicket for a single
comes forward and drives it to sweeper cover for a single
comes forward and looks to drive it and gets an inside edge
comes forward and drives it to sweeper cover for a single
good length ball on the off stump. Anderson defends it back to the bowler
cuts it to deep point for a single
short ball on the off stump. Anderson stands tall and pulls it into the stands for a six. The crowd go silent for a few seconds to absorb the impact of that stroke
good length ball on the off stump. Anderson comes forward with the front foot pointing towards the cover region and brings up the stroke of the innings. Picture perfect follow through
defends it to cover
fuller ball outside the off stump. Anderson cuts it to sweeper cover for a couple
drives it to sweeper cover for a single
comes forward and punches it to cover for a single
bounce and turn right away as Anderson runs it down to short third-man where Razzak misfields to give them an extra run
comes forward and drives it to cover
fuller ball on the leg stump. Anderson goes down on one knee and lofts it  to deep midwicket for a boundary
fuller ball outside the off stump. Anderson comes forward and drives it to cover
darted on a fuller length on the middle stump. Corey moves back and defends it back to the bowler
comes forward and drives it  to cover. That's a good over as there were three dot balls to end the over
comes forward and drives it to long-on for a single
fuller ball on the off stump. Anderson clears the front foot and swings it over long on for a six. A much needed  one at that
defends it to cover
lofts it to long-on for a single
fuller ball on the off stump. Anderson lofts it over long-on for another six. He is looking very dangerous and Bangladesh need to get him soon if they want to go on and win the game from here on
fuller ball on the off stump. Elliot comes forward and lofts it inside out over cover for a boundary
Elliot is coming down the track as Gazi is about to bowl and the bowler shortens his length but to no avail as Elliot cuts it to sweeper cover for a boundary
paddles it to short fine-leg for a single
pushes it to the leg side for a single
off the outside edge to short third-man for a single
another six! Anderson is slowly taking the game away from Bangladesh. Gazi flights the ball and lands it on the middle stump. Anderson deposits it into the deep mid wicket stand
looks to cut and is beaten
comes forward and drives it to long-on for a single

what a wicket! Anderson is looking for one shot too many as he is foxed by the slower one on the leg stump. Anderson swings and is half way into his follow through by the time the ball crashes onto the middle stump. Is this the breakthrough that Bangladesh were looking for?

is that the game for Bangladesh? Rubel has certainly turned it around for them. He bowls what seems an innocous delivery, but the ball rushes to him and McCullum slices  straight into the waiting hands of the fielder at backward point

that's a hat-trick for Rubel! This is as lucky as anyone can get as he bowls one down the leg side and Neesham tries to flick it and gets a faint edge back to the keeper. Rahim does well to dive to his right and take a brilliant catch. That's effectively game over for New Zealand
comes forward and drives it to cover
pushes it to mid-off for a single
comes forward and drives it to long-on for a single
comes forward and drives it back to the bowler
fuller ball outside the off stump. Nathan pushes it to point
comes down the track and defends it
comes forward and pushes it to mid-on
good length ball outside the off stump. Elliot pushes it to short third-man and sets off for a quick single
fuller ball on the off stump. McCullum pushes it to mid-on
fuller ball on the leg stump. Nathan pushes to mid-on, this time with soft hands, and sets off for a quick single
that's a snorter! Rubel nearly had his fifth as he had Elliot to fend it off the helmet grill. The resulting edge just falls short of Rahim who ran to where short third-man would've been
comes forward and defends it to the leg side
beaten by the turn outside the off stump
good length ball on the off stump. Elliot slog-sweeps it over deep mid wicket and gets to his fifty in style
comes forward and drives it to long-on for a single
comes down the track and drives it back to the bowler
short ball outside the off stump. Nathan makes room and smashes it to deep point for a boundary
fuller ball outside the off stump. McCullum swings. If he got the bat on the ball, it would have sailed over deep mid wicket. He was beaten by the turn
lofts it to long-off for a single
comes down the track and lofts it to long-on for a couple
good length ball outside the off stump. Nathan swings and misses, once again
comes forward and drives it to long-on for a couple

Rubel does have his fifth! McCullum looks to wield the long handle and clears the front foot. He lofts it and it doesn't clear the fielder at mid-off. This has to be right up there as the best spell by a Bangladesh bowler. Brilliant bowling as he has run through the middle order and the lower middle order of New Zealand
comes forward and pulls it to deep mid wicket for a  single
short ball on the leg stump. That's a gift by Razzak. Elliot pulls it to deep square-leg for a boundary
slices it to deep point for a single
short ball on the leg stump. Southee, under pressure to get going from ball one pulls and finds the fielder at deep midwicket.
flighted ball on the middle stump. Elliot lofts it over deep mid wicket for his second six
retains the strike with a push to the leg side
slower and fuller outside the off stump. He looks to slog it and is beaten
lofts it to long-on for a single
comes forward and turns it  to square-leg for a single

fuller ball on the off stump. Elliot lofts and how fitting is it that Mashrafe takes the catch, a brilliant catch, as his record is the one that Rubel equals for the best figures by a Bangladesh bowler. Brilliant spell by Rubel, five wickets in it
